lback.\",\"maxIterations\":5,\"convergenceThreshold\":0.05,\"stuckThreshold\":3,\"specFolder\":\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research\",\"loopType\":\"research\",\"stopPolicy\":\"convergence\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-glm52-1-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"lineageLabel\":\"glm52-1\",\"executor\":{\"kind\":\"cli-opencode\",\"model\":\"zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2\",\"reasoningEffort\":\"max\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-07-08T00:00:00Z\"}","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/glm52-1/deep-research-state.jsonl","text":"{\"type\":\"config\",\"topic\":\"Validate and stress-test the merge design for folding deep-loop-runtime into deep-loop-workflows as system-deep-loop: structural layout, bidirectional path-coupling repair, the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow, reference migration across commands/agents/READMEs/advisor-corpus, and whether fallback-router.ts should be wired for real GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback.\",\"maxIterations\":5,\"convergenceThreshold\":0.05,\"stuckThreshold\":3,\"specFolder\":\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research\",\"loopType\":\"research\",\"stopPolicy\":\"convergence\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-glm52-1-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"lineageLabel\":\"glm52-1\",\"executor\":{\"kind\":\"cli-opencode\",\"model\":\"zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2\",\"reasoningEffort\":\"max\"},\"createdAt\":\"2026-07-08T00:00:00Z\"}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":1,"totalLines":1,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/glm52-1/deep-research-state.jsonl","time":{"start":1783488240352,"end":1783488240362}},"id":"prt_f402edadf001DZ0qweyf8GaEPA","sessionID":"ses_0bfd247cdffejTvcrmloecAup3","messageID":"msg_f402ea004001137WN4TQPOGgtt"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783488240363,"sessionID":"ses_0bfd247cdffejTvcrmloecAup3","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_6165d61c07024521996b24d2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/glm52-1/deep-research-strategy.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/glm52-1/deep-research-strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deep Research Strategy — glm52-1 Lineage\n2: \n3: ## Research Topic\n4: \n5: Validate and stress-test the merge design for folding `deep-loop-runtime` into `deep-loop-workflows` as `system-deep-loop`: structural layout, bidirectional path-coupling repair, the `system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow, reference migration across commands/agents/READMEs/advisor-corpus, and whether `fallback-router.ts` should be wired for real GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback.\n6: \n7: ## Known Context\n8: \n9: - **Two skills today:** `deep-loop-workflows` (hub, advisor-routable, 4 active workflow families: research/review/ai-council/improvement) consumes `deep-loop-runtime` (frozen, MCP-free backend). [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/SKILL.md:12]\n10: - **Merge target:** fold the runtime INTO the workflows skill, renaming the result to `system-deep-loop`. [SOURCE: spec.md:57]\n11: - **This phase is strictly read-only** — no merge execution; this research validates/extends the design produced by 3 parallel Sonnet-5 Plan agents. [SOURCE: spec.md:69-75]\n12: - **Bidirectional coupling confirmed:** `deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/scripts/orchestrate-*.cjs` require `../../../deep-loop-runtime/lib/council/*.cjs` (5+ seam files). [SOURCE: grep hits]\n13: - **fallback-router.ts zero callers:** Only tests (`fallback-router.vitest.ts`, `executor-provenance-mismatch.vitest.ts`) and docs import it; no `.cjs` runtime script or production `.ts` path calls `resolveFallback`/`createFallbackRouter`. [SOURCE: grep across .opencode/skills; spec.md:124]\n14: - **artifact-root.cjs is a re-export seam:** `deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/artifact-root.cjs` re-exports from `../../../system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs`. [SOURCE: artifact-root.cjs:17-18]\n15: - **node_modules borrow:** runtime reaches into system-spec-kit's internal node_modules for zod/better-sqlite3/tsx (8+ reach-ins). [SOURCE: 117-improvement-research findings]\n16: - **Commands invoke runtime scripts:** `deep/{research,review,ai-council}.md` shell out to `deep-loop-runtime/scripts/render-command-contract.cjs`. [SOURCE: .opencode/commands/deep/*.md]\n17: - resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate.\n18: \n19: ## Key Questions\n20: \n21: - Q1: Is the structural layout (fold runtime into workflows as system-deep-loop) mechanically safe, and where does each component land?\n22: - Q2: How many bidirectional path-couplings exist between the two skills, and what breaks silently if not repaired?\n23: - Q3: How does the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow behave post-merge — net simplification or net risk transfer?\n24: - Q4: What is the full reference-migration surface and the risk of incomplete migration?\n25: - Q5: Should fallback-router.ts be wired for real GLM-5.2 -> MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback?\n26: \n27: ## Answered Questions\n28: \n29: (none yet)\n30: \n31: ## What Worked\n32: \n33: (filled per iteration)\n34: \n35: ## What Failed\n36: \n37: (filled per iteration)\n38: \n39: ## Exhausted Approaches\n40: \n41: (none yet)\n42: \n43: ## Ruled-Out Directions\n44: \n45: (none yet)\n46: \n47: ## Next Focus\n48: \n49: Iteration 1: Map the full structural layout — enumerate every directory and file under both skills, classify what folds where, and verify the merge is mechanically safe (no orphaned entry points, no path-depth assumptions that break).\n\n(End of file - total 49 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deep Research Strategy — glm52-1 Lineage\n\n## Research Topic\n\nValidate and stress-test the merge design for folding `deep-loop-runtime` into `deep-loop-workflows` as `system-deep-loop`: structural layout, bidirectional path-coupling repair, the `system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow, reference migration across commands/agents/READMEs/advisor-corpus, and whether `fallback-router.ts` should be wired for real GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback.\n\n## Known Context\n\n- **Two skills today:** `deep-loop-workflows` (hub, advisor-routable, 4 active workflow families: research/review/ai-council/improvement) consumes `deep-loop-runtime` (frozen, MCP-free backend). [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/SKILL.md:12]\n- **Merge target:** fold the runtime INTO the workflows skill, renaming the result to `system-deep-loop`. [SOURCE: spec.md:57]\n- **This phase is strictly read-only** — no merge execution; this research validates/extends the design produced by 3 parallel Sonnet-5 Plan agents. [SOURCE: spec.md:69-75]\n- **Bidirectional coupling confirmed:** `deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/scripts/orchestrate-*.cjs` require `../../../deep-loop-runtime/lib/council/*.cjs` (5+ seam files). [SOURCE: grep hits]\n- **fallback-router.ts zero callers:** Only tests (`fallback-router.vitest.ts`, `executor-provenance-mismatch.vitest.ts`) and docs import it; no `.cjs` runtime script or production `.ts` path calls `resolveFallback`/`createFallbackRouter`. [SOURCE: grep across .opencode/skills; spec.md:124]\n- **artifact-root.cjs is a re-export seam:** `deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/artifact-root.cjs` re-exports from `../../../system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs`. [SOURCE: artifact-root.cjs:17-18]\n- **node_modules borrow:** runtime reaches into system-spec-kit's internal node_modules for zod/better-sqlite3/tsx (8+ reach-ins). [SOURCE: 117-improvement-research findings]\n- **Commands invoke runtime scripts:** `deep/{research,review,ai-council}.md` shell out to `deep-loop-runtime/scripts/render-command-contract.cjs`. [SOURCE: .opencode/commands/deep/*.md]\n- resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate.\n\n## Key Questions\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/glm52-1/deep-research-strategy.md","text":"# Deep Research Strategy — glm52-1 Lineage\n\n## Research Topic\n\nValidate and stress-test the merge design for folding `deep-loop-runtime` into `deep-loop-workflows` as `system-deep-loop`: structural layout, bidirectional path-coupling repair, the `system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow, reference migration across commands/agents/READMEs/advisor-corpus, and whether `fallback-router.ts` should be wired for real GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback.\n\n## Known Context\n\n- **Two skills today:** `deep-loop-workflows` (hub, advisor-routable, 4 active workflow families: research/review/ai-council/improvement) consumes `deep-loop-runtime` (frozen, MCP-free backend). [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/SKILL.md:12]\n- **Merge target:** fold the runtime INTO the workflows skill, renaming the result to `system-deep-loop`. [SOURCE: spec.md:57]\n- **This phase is strictly read-only** — no merge execution; this research validates/extends the design produced by 3 parallel Sonnet-5 Plan agents. [SOURCE: spec.md:69-75]\n- **Bidirectional coupling confirmed:** `deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/scripts/orchestrate-*.cjs` require `../../../deep-loop-runtime/lib/council/*.cjs` (5+ seam files). [SOURCE: grep hits]\n- **fallback-router.ts zero callers:** Only tests (`fallback-router.vitest.ts`, `executor-provenance-mismatch.vitest.ts`) and docs import it; no `.cjs` runtime script or production `.ts` path calls `resolveFallback`/`createFallbackRouter`. [SOURCE: grep across .opencode/skills; spec.md:124]\n- **artifact-root.cjs is a re-export seam:** `deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/artifact-root.cjs` re-exports from `../../../system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs`. [SOURCE: artifact-root.cjs:17-18]\n- **node_modules borrow:** runtime reaches into system-spec-kit's internal node_modules for zod/better-sqlite3/tsx (8+ reach-ins). [SOURCE: 117-improvement-research findings]\n- **Commands invoke runtime scripts:** `deep/{research,review,ai-council}.md` shell out to `deep-loop-runtime/scripts/render-command-contract.cjs`. [SOURCE: .opencode/commands/deep/*.md]\n- resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate.\n\n## Key Questions\n\n- Q1: Is the structural layout (fold runtime into workflows as system-deep-loop) mechanically safe, and where does each component land?\n- Q2: How many bidirectional path-couplings exist between the two skills, and what breaks silently if not repaired?\n- Q3: How does the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow behave post-merge — net simplification or net risk transfer?\n- Q4: What is the full reference-migration surface and the risk of incomplete migration?\n- Q5: Should fallback-router.ts be wired for real GLM-5.2 -> MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback?\n\n## Answered Questions\n\n(none yet)\n\n## What Worked\n\n(filled per iteration)\n\n## What Failed\n\n(filled per iteration)\n\n## Exhausted Approaches\n\n(none yet)\n\n## Ruled-Out Directions\n\n(none yet)\n\n## Next Focus\n\nIteration 1: Map the full structural layout — enumerate every directory and file under both skills, classify what folds where, and verify the merge is mechanically safe (no orphaned entry points, no path-depth assumptions that break).","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":49,"totalLines":49,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/glm52-1/deep-research-strategy.md","time":{"start":1783488240350,"end":1783488240362}},"id":"prt_f402edadc001Nljr0B0LFK4693","sessionID":"ses_0bfd247cdffejTvcrmloecAup3","messageID":"msg_f402ea004001137WN4TQPOGgtt"}}
