seat_diversity_patterns.md',\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/compile-command-contracts.cjs:73:      '.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/assets/deep_ai_council_config.json',\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/compile-command-contracts.cjs:74:      '.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/assets/prompt_pack_round.md',\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/compile-command-contracts.cjs:75:      '.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/assets/runtime_capabilities.json',\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/compile-command-contracts.cjs:168:    modeSkillPath: '.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/SKILL.md',\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/compile-command-contracts.cjs:170:    promptPackPath: '.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl',\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/compile-command-contracts.cjs:179:      '.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/SKILL.md',\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/compile-command-contracts.cjs:180:      '.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md',\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/compile-command-contracts.cjs:181:      '.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_format.md',\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/compile-command-contracts.cjs:182:      '.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/review_mode_contract.yaml',\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/compile-command-contracts.cjs:183:      '.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/convergence/convergence.md',\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/compile-command-contracts.cjs:184:      '.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_config.json',\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/compile-command-contracts.cjs:185:      '.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl',\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/compile-command-contracts.cjs:270:    modeSkillPath: '.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/SKILL.md',\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/compile-command-contracts.cjs:272:    promptPackPath: '.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl',\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/compile-command-contracts.cjs:281:      '.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/SKILL.md',\n\n=== workflows -> runtime ===\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/SKILL.md:4:description: \"Unified deep-loop workflow skill: routes active requests to research, review, ai-council, and improvement modes over the shared deep-loop-runtime backend.\"\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/SKILL.md:12:One skill, four active workflow families, one shared backend. `deep-loop-workflows` is the public, advisor-routable home for active deep-loop personas; `deep-loop-runtime` is the frozen, MCP-free backend it consumes. This hub holds NO per-mode convergence, state, or synthesis logic — each active mode keeps its own contract in its packet, and the hub only routes by `workflowMode` through `mode-registry.json`.\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/SKILL.md:31:- Backend/runtime support (executor, coverage-graph, scoring, fan-out) — that is `deep-loop-runtime`, consumed here, not invoked as a user workflow.\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/SKILL.md:43:- **`runtimeLoopType`** — the graph-backed convergence key consumed by `deep-loop-runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs` (validated against active `research|review|council`). **Explicit `null` for all four improvement lanes; never inferred from `workflowMode`.** Note `ai-council` maps to `runtimeLoopType: council`.\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/SKILL.md:85:All modes consume `deep-loop-runtime` (frozen, MCP-free): executor config, prompt-pack, validation, atomic state, coverage-graph, Bayesian scoring, fan-out, the council primitives, and the promoted plumbing (capability resolver, artifact-root, loop-lock CLI, lifecycle taxonomy). The runtime never gains an `improvement` loopType — improvement stays host-driven.\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/SKILL.md:99:- **NEVER** add an `improvement` `loopType` to `deep-loop-runtime/convergence.cjs` (improvement is host-driven; `runtimeLoopType` stays `null`).\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/SKILL.md:112:- Backend: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/` (frozen, consumed by every mode).\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/SKILL.md:138:- `deep-loop-runtime` is the frozen, MCP-free backend every mode consumes.\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/feature_catalog/08--council-graph-integration/council-graph-upsert-idempotency-and-self-loop-rejection.md:31:Current behavior is grounded in `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/upsert.cjs`, which the scenario identifies as runtime CLI script: idempotent upsert + self-loop rejection. Validation is anchored by `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/integration/council-graph-script.vitest.ts`, covering test: \"upserts prompt-safe council graph data and queries unresolved disagreements and decision support\".\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/feature_catalog/08--council-graph-integration/council-graph-upsert-idempotency-and-self-loop-rejection.md:43:| `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/upsert.cjs` | Handler | runtime CLI script: idempotent upsert + self-loop rejection |\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/feature_catalog/08--council-graph-integration/council-graph-upsert-idempotency-and-self-loop-rejection.md:44:| `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/council/council-graph-db.ts` | Library | Storage layer: unique constraints |\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/feature_catalog/08--council-graph-integration/council-graph-upsert-idempotency-and-self-loop-rejection.md:45:| `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/upsert.cjs` | Runtime CLI | Input validation and edge normalization |\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/feature_catalog/08--council-graph-integration/council-graph-upsert-idempotency-and-self-loop-rejection.md:52:| `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/integration/council-graph-script.vitest.ts` | Automated test | Test: \"upserts prompt-safe council graph data and queries unresolved disagreements and decision support\" |\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/description.json:3:  \"description\": \"Unified deep-loop workflow parent hub: the single advisor-routable home for active deep-loop personas, routing to seven modes across four workflow families over the shared deep-loop-runtime backend. research (outward web+code iterative investigation → research/ artifacts), review (iterative review loop → P0/P1/P2 findings + verdict), ai-council (multi-seat planning deliberation → ai-council/ artifacts), and four improvement lanes on the deep-improvement packet (agent-improvement, model-benchmark, skill-benchmark, ai-system-improvement). The hub holds no per-mode convergence, state, or synthesis logic; each mode keeps its own contract in its packet and is reachable via its /deep:* command and native agent.\",\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:351:Verify mk-spec-memory has no council graph MCP entries and council graph operations route through `deep-loop-runtime --loop-type council`.\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:409:| `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/integration/council-graph-script.vitest.ts` | DAC-019, DAC-020, DAC-021, DAC-022, DAC-023, DAC-024 |\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:410:| `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/integration/council-graph-value-scenarios.