deep-loop-workflows/README.md:92:| `deep-loop-runtime` | The frozen, MCP-free backend the modes run on. |\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/assets/deep_ai_council_config.json:37:    \"owner\": \"deep-loop-runtime\",\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/feature_catalog/08--council-graph-integration/council-graph-query-hostile-metadata-redaction.md:31:Current behavior is grounded in `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/council/council-graph-query.ts`, which the scenario identifies as allowlist + length bounds (p1-003 remediation). Validation is anchored by `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/integration/council-graph-script.vitest.ts`, covering test: \"redacts arbitrary metadata from prompt-safe query output\".\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/feature_catalog/08--council-graph-integration/council-graph-query-hostile-metadata-redaction.md:43:| `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/council/council-graph-query.ts` | Library | Allowlist + length bounds (P1-003 remediation) |\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/feature_catalog/08--council-graph-integration/council-graph-query-hostile-metadata-redaction.md:44:| `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/query.cjs` | Handler | runtime CLI script: prompt-safe query envelope |\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/feature_catalog/08--council-graph-integration/council-graph-query-hostile-metadata-redaction.md:52:| `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/integration/council-graph-script.vitest.ts` | Automated test | Test: \"redacts arbitrary metadata from prompt-safe query output\" |\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/SKILL.md:126:- `scripts/` contains deterministic helpers; scripts are invoked explicitly and are not markdown-routed. Notable entries: `persist-artifacts.cjs` (artifact writer CLI), `replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs` (DAC-025 derived-projection rebuild — reads `ai-council-state.jsonl` and writes through `deep-loop-runtime/scripts/upsert.cjs --loop-type council`, with `--dry-run` for payload inspection).\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/SKILL.md:390:   - Graph updates belong to caller-owned `deep-loop-runtime` CLI reducers, not council-seat deliberation.\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/SKILL.md:411:- `references/convergence/deep_mode.md` - deep-mode session/topic/round hierarchy, state files, cost guards and the deep-loop-runtime dependency.\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/SKILL.md:483:- `references/integration/graph_support.md` - derived graph support and deep-loop-runtime CLI boundary.\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/graph-metadata.json:10:        \"target\": \"deep-loop-runtime\",\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/graph-metadata.json:29:        \"target\": \"deep-loop-runtime\",\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/graph-metadata.json:43:    \"depends_on\": [\"deep-loop-runtime\"],\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/graph-metadata.json:139:        \"name\": \"deep-loop-runtime\",\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/graph-metadata.json:141:        \"path\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md\",\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/graph-metadata.json:145:    \"causal_summary\": \"deep-loop-workflows is the single public skill that merges active deep-loop persona modes (deep-research, deep-review, deep-ai-council, deep-improvement) into one advisor identity with active mode packets, routed by workflowMode through mode-registry.json over the frozen MCP-free deep-loop-runtime backend. @context owns one-shot retrieval while research and review carry bounded context snapshots. Per-mode convergence, state, artifacts, and tool-permission contracts are preserved unflattened; the three-tier discriminator (workflowMode / runtimeLoopType / backendKind) keeps graph-backed modes and improvement-host/external-adapter modes distinct.\",\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/feature_catalog/08--council-graph-integration/council-graph-convergence-three-state-decision-matrix.md:31:Current behavior is grounded in `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs`, which the scenario identifies as runtime CLI script: three-state decision logic. Validation is anchored by `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/integration/council-graph-script.vitest.ts`, covering tests: \"allows convergence when ... thresholds are met\", \"continues convergence when non-blocking thresholds are not met\", \"blocks convergence for empty derived graphs...\".\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/feature_catalog/08--council-graph-integration/council-graph-convergence-three-state-decision-matrix.md:43:| `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs` | Handler | runtime CLI script: three-state decision logic |\n","exit":0,"truncated":false},"title":"cd /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public; echo \"=== runtime -> workflows ===\"; rg -n \"deep-loop-workflows\" .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts -g '!node_modules' 2>/dev/null | head -40; echo; echo \"=== workflows -> runtime ===\"; rg -n \"deep-loop-runtime\" .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows -g '!node_modules' 2>/dev/null | head -40","time":{"start":1783488283186,"end":1783488283190}},"id":"prt_f402f81d0001edxWqrWAzT7nAA","sessionID":"ses_0bfd247cdffejTvcrmloecAup3","messageID":"msg_f402f3110001GTp6uDyFzZUjf7"}}
