 sample projection of 43 percent.\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/changelog/v1.2.0.0.md:53:| `feature_catalog/01--executor/fallback-router.md` + `05--scoring/bayesian-scorer.md` + `03--validation/post-dispatch-validate.md` | description-drift fixes (+ matching playbook OVERVIEW lines); other 14 catalog entries verified accurate in the full-17 sweep |\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/graph-metadata.json:112:      \"fallback-router\",\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/executor-provenance-mismatch.vitest.ts:12:import { type ModelProfile, type ModelRegistry, resolveFallback } from '../../lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.js';\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/executor-provenance-mismatch.vitest.ts:237:describe('fallback-router approval guard (008)', () => {\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/executor-provenance-mismatch.vitest.ts:245:    expect(resolveFallback('swe-1.6', registry, ['swe-1.6', 'haiku'])).toEqual({\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/executor-provenance-mismatch.vitest.ts:253:    const route = resolveFallback('swe-1.6', registry, ['swe-1.6']);\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/executor-provenance-mismatch.vitest.ts:259:    expect(resolveFallback('swe-1.6', registry)).toEqual({\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/README.md:30:| `fallback-router.vitest.ts` | `lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts` |\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/README.md:92:`lib/deep-loop/` holds the loop infrastructure. `executor-config` parses per-iteration executor settings from a shared schema so every consumer calls the same executor shape. `executor-audit` appends a provenance block to each iteration JSONL so you can tell which model and CLI produced each iteration. `prompt-pack` renders the iteration prompt template. `post-dispatch-validate` checks that an iteration produced valid markdown, JSONL and delta outputs before the state log accepts them, stamps seekable log-region offsets, and quarantines failed LLM-judge fallback cards. `atomic-state` writes state logs through a tmpfile-plus-rename pattern, adds compare-before-write, SHA-256 integrity helpers, and a deferred writer, so a crash never leaves a partial line and unchanged snapshots can avoid redundant writes. `jsonl-repair` recovers a corrupt trailing line before append and supports lock-held fan-out salvage merges. `loop-lock` enforces single-writer access around state mutations, with heartbeat metadata and opt-in host-local single-flight acquisition. `permissions-gate` checks permission scope before touching sensitive paths. `bayesian-scorer` exports the small Bayesian helpers `computeScore` and `shouldDemote`; `convergence.cjs` builds the typed loop decisions. `fallback-router` picks a replacement executor when the primary one times out and validates typed reroute graphs before dispatch.\n","metadata":{"output":"=== runtime -> system-spec-kit ===\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/check-contract-drift.cjs:39:  '.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/workflows/auto_mode_contract.md',\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/compile-command-contracts.cjs:14:  autoModeContract: '.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/workflows/auto_mode_contract.md',\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/compile-command-contracts.cjs:491:        'classifierPath: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/gate-3-classifier.ts',\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/artifact-root.cjs:6:// ║ single implementation continues to live in system-spec-kit; the runtime  ║\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/artifact-root.cjs:18:  path.join(__dirname, '..', '..', '..', 'system-spec-kit', 'shared', 'review-research-paths.cjs'),\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/README.md:3:description: \"Maintainer map for deep-loop runtime helpers moved out of system-spec-kit MCP server.\"\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/README.md:15:`lib/deep-loop/` is the migrated runtime home for deep-review and deep-research loop helpers. Legacy references to `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/deep-loop/` should point here unless they specifically describe old provenance.\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/README.md:33:| `artifact-root.cjs` | Canonical seam for the artifact-topology resolver (`resolveArtifactRoot`). The single implementation stays in `system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs`; the research, review and context reducers import it from here so the dependency points at the backend. |\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/README.md:41:- Spec Kit runtime: `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/memory/bounded-cache.ts`, `audit-rotation.ts`, `lib/runtime/timer-registry.ts`, `shutdown-hooks.ts`.\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/README.md:42:- Ops: `system-spec-kit/scripts/ops/process-memory-harness.ts`, `process-sweep.ts`.\n\n=== fallback-router callers ===\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/README.md:31:| `fallback-router.ts` | Executor fallback routing. |\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:320:export function createFallbackRouter(\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:332:      return resolveFallback(failedModelId, registry, approvedModelIds, context);\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:357:export function resolveFallback(\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/fallback-router.vitest.ts:8:  createFallbackRouter,\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/fallback-router.vitest.ts:11:  resolveFallback,\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/fallback-router.vitest.ts:12:} from '../../lib/deep-loop/fallback-router';\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/fallback-router.vitest.ts:36:describe('fallback-router', () => {\n.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/fallback-router.vitest.ts:38:    expect(resolveFallback('swe-1.6', registryWithFallback('swe-1