{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783488555433,"sessionID":"ses_0bfd247cdffejTvcrmloecAup3","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"edit","callID":"call_9488a326423246899f4e4546","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/glm52-3/deep-research-strategy.md","newString":"## Answered Questions\n\n- Q1 (iteration 1): Mechanically safe. Runtime relocates as self-contained `runtime/` subtree. THREE distinct path-repair mechanisms identified (see F1.2). spec.md:132 asymmetry confirmed.\n\n## What Worked\n\n- Mechanism-classification audit (iteration 1): separating absolute-string sites from relative-require sites exposed that the plan conflates them. 8-10 file reads + targeted rg gave full coverage.\n\n## What Failed\n\n(none yet)\n\n## Exhausted Approaches\n\n(none yet)\n\n## Ruled-Out Directions\n\n- R1.1 (iteration 1): Single mechanical find/replace across all coupling — breaks class A absolute-string sites.\n- R1.2 (iteration 1): Treating reverse direction as larger per-site risk — uniform mechanism; forward single site riskier.\n\n## Next Focus\n\nIteration 2: Complete Q2's coupling-COUNT and Q3's tooling-borrow depth math. Verify whether class (D) reverse sites ALL follow the uniform 3→2 / 4→3 pattern with zero exceptions, and compute the exact post-merge `__dirname` arithmetic for the artifact-root.cjs +1-hop and the system-spec-kit test:council include-glob impact (REQ-003 risk). Resolves Q2 and Q3.","oldString":"## Answered Questions\n\n(none yet)\n\n## What Worked\n\n(filled per iteration)\n\n## What Failed\n\n(filled per iteration)\n\n## Exhausted Approaches\n\n(none yet)\n\n## Ruled-Out Directions\n\n(none yet)\n\n## Next Focus\n\nIteration 1: Verify the structural layout is mechanically safe by enumerating runtime's components and confirming WHERE each lands after nesting, plus audit every RELATIVE `require()`/`path.join(__dirname...)` hop (the ones that actually break) vs the absolute-path string sites (which survive untouched). Resolves Q1 and the mechanism half of Q2."},"output":"Edit applied successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"diff":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/glm52-3/deep-research-strategy.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/glm52-3/deep-research-strategy.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/glm52-3/deep-research-strategy.md\n@@ -39,29 +39,30 @@\n - convergence threshold met after the minIterations floor (3).\n \n ## Answered Questions\n \n-(none yet)\n+- Q1 (iteration 1): Mechanically safe. Runtime relocates as self-contained `runtime/` subtree. THREE distinct path-repair mechanisms identified (see F1.2). spec.md:132 asymmetry confirmed.\n \n ## What Worked\n \n-(filled per iteration)\n+- Mechanism-classification audit (iteration 1): separating absolute-string sites from relative-require sites exposed that the plan conflates them. 8-10 file reads + targeted rg gave full coverage.\n \n ## What Failed\n \n-(filled per iteration)\n+(none yet)\n \n ## Exhausted Approaches\n \n (none yet)\n \n ## Ruled-Out Directions\n \n-(none yet)\n+- R1.1 (iteration 1): Single mechanical find/replace across all coupling — breaks class A absolute-string sites.\n+- R1.2 (iteration 1): Treating reverse direction as larger per-site risk — uniform mechanism; forward single site riskier.\n \n ## Next Focus\n \n-Iteration 1: Verify the structural layout is mechanically safe by enumerating runtime's components and confirming WHERE each lands after nesting, plus audit every RELATIVE `require()`/`path.join(__dirname...)` hop (the ones that actually break) vs the absolute-path string sites (which survive untouched). Resolves Q1 and the mechanism half of Q2.\n+Iteration 2: Complete Q2's coupling-COUNT and Q3's tooling-borrow depth math. Verify whether class (D) reverse sites ALL follow the uniform 3→2 / 4→3 pattern with zero exceptions, and compute the exact post-merge `__dirname` arithmetic for the artifact-root.cjs +1-hop and the system-spec-kit test:council include-glob impact (REQ-003 risk). Resolves Q2 and Q3.\n \n ## Research Boundaries\n \n - Max iterations: 5\n","filediff":{"file":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/glm52-3/deep-research-strategy.md","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/glm52-3/deep-research-strategy.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/glm52-3/deep-research-strategy.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/glm52-3/deep-research-strategy.md\n@@ -39,29 +39,30 @@\n - convergence threshold met after the minIterations floor (3).\n \n ## Answered Questions\n \n-(none yet)\n+- Q1 (iteration 1): Mechanically safe. Runtime relocates as self-contained `runtime/` subtree. THREE distinct path-repair mechanisms identified (see F1.2). spec.md:132 asymmetry confirmed.\n \n ## What Worked\n \n-(filled per iteration)\n+- Mechanism-classification audit (iteration 1): separating absolute-string sites from relative-require sites exposed that the plan conflates them. 8-10 file reads + targeted rg gave full coverage.\n \n ## What Failed\n \n-(filled per iteration)\n+(none yet)\n \n ## Exhausted Approaches\n \n (none yet)\n \n ## Ruled-Out Directions\n \n-(none yet)\n+- R1.1 (iteration 1): Single mechanical find/replace across all coupling — breaks class A absolute-string sites.\n+- R1.2 (iteration 1): Treating reverse direction as larger per-site risk — uniform mechanism; forward single site riskier.\n \n ## Next Focus\n \n-Iteration 1: Verify the structural layout is mechanically safe by enumerating runtime's components and confirming WHERE each lands after nesting, plus audit every RELATIVE `require()`/`path.join(__dirname...)` hop (the ones that actually break) vs the absolute-path string sites (which survive untouched). Resolves Q1 and the mechanism half of Q2.\n+Iteration 2: Complete Q2's coupling-COUNT and Q3's tooling-borrow depth math. Verify whether class (D) reverse sites ALL follow the uniform 3→2 / 4→3 pattern with zero exceptions, and compute the exact post-merge `__dirname` arithmetic for the artifact-root.cjs +1-hop and the system-spec-kit test:council include-glob impact (REQ-003 risk). Resolves Q2 and Q3.\n \n ## Research Boundaries\n \n - Max iterations: 5\n","additions":6,"deletions":5},"truncated":false},"title":".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/glm52-3/deep-research-strategy.md","time":{"start":1783488555430,"end":1783488555432}},"id":"prt_f4033a9a2001u2EC0DyGikLqQp","sessionID":"ses_0bfd247cdffejTvcrmloecAup3","messageID":"msg_f4033610000145n2yh76uYyAXO"}}
