{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783488707473,"sessionID":"ses_0bfd247cdffejTvcrmloecAup3","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"edit","callID":"call_d6732b5ea3c04f38a8e5d65f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/glm52-3/deep-research-strategy.md","newString":"## Answered Questions\n\n- Q1 (iteration 1): Mechanically safe. Runtime relocates as self-contained `runtime/` subtree. THREE distinct path-repair mechanisms identified (see F1.2). spec.md:132 asymmetry confirmed.\n- Q2 (iteration 2): 41 grep hits in reverse direction but only ~12 CODE sites (uniform mechanism) + 1 absolute shell-out (replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs:26) + ~28 test-fixture/comment strings needing semantic review. Forward: ~40+ absolute-string sites + 1 relative require.\n- Q3 (iteration 2): Net NEUTRAL. node_modules tooling-borrow already shipped (runtime has own node_modules). Only the artifact-root.cjs LOGIC seam remains, +1 hop post-merge. Keep the borrow, fix the hop, document the seam.\n\n## What Worked\n\n- Mechanism-classification audit (iteration 1): separating absolute-string sites from relative-require sites exposed that the plan conflates them. 8-10 file reads + targeted rg gave full coverage.\n- system-spec-kit surface enumeration (iteration 2): reading vitest.config.ts + package.json test:council + the council-playbook anchor test caught the 4→9 undercount that a grep-only audit would miss.\n\n## What Failed\n\n(none yet)\n\n## Exhausted Approaches\n\n(none yet)\n\n## Ruled-Out Directions\n\n- R1.1 (iteration 1): Single mechanical find/replace across all coupling — breaks class A absolute-string sites.\n- R1.2 (iteration 1): Treating reverse direction as larger per-site risk — uniform mechanism; forward single site riskier.\n- R2.1 (iteration 2): Mechanism A (absolute-string) is forward-only — refuted by replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs:26 reverse shell-out.\n- R2.2 (iteration 2): \"4 system-spec-kit edits suffice for REQ-003\" — real surface ~9 sites/5 files.\n\n## Next Focus\n\nIteration 3: Q4 reference-migration surface — enumerate commands/.opencode/agents/.claude/agents, root + skill READMEs, the mk-deep-loop-guard plugin, git hooks, CI, and (highest-risk) system-skill-advisor routing corpus (labeled-prompts.jsonl, divergence ledger, hardcoded scorer constants). Quantify the ~948-hit surface from spec.md:88 and assess incomplete-migration risk per surface. Resolves Q4.","oldString":"## Answered Questions\n\n- Q1 (iteration 1): Mechanically safe. Runtime relocates as self-contained `runtime/` subtree. THREE distinct path-repair mechanisms identified (see F1.2). spec.md:132 asymmetry confirmed.\n\n## What Worked\n\n- Mechanism-classification audit (iteration 1): separating absolute-string sites from relative-require sites exposed that the plan conflates them. 8-10 file reads + targeted rg gave full coverage.\n\n## What Failed\n\n(none yet)\n\n## Exhausted Approaches\n\n(none yet)\n\n## Ruled-Out Directions\n\n- R1.1 (iteration 1): Single mechanical find/replace across all coupling — breaks class A absolute-string sites.\n- R1.2 (iteration 1): Treating reverse direction as larger per-site risk — uniform mechanism; forward single site riskier.\n\n## Next Focus\n\nIteration 2: Complete Q2's coupling-COUNT and Q3's tooling-borrow depth math. Verify whether class (D) reverse sites ALL follow the uniform 3→2 / 4→3 pattern with zero exceptions, and compute the exact post-merge `__dirname` arithmetic for the artifact-root.cjs +1-hop and the system-spec-kit test:council include-glob impact (REQ-003 risk). Resolves Q2 and Q3."},"output":"Edit applied successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"diff":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/glm52-3/deep-research-strategy.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/glm52-3/deep-research-strategy.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/glm52-3/deep-research-strategy.md\n@@ -40,12 +40,15 @@\n \n ## Answered Questions\n \n - Q1 (iteration 1): Mechanically safe. Runtime relocates as self-contained `runtime/` subtree. THREE distinct path-repair mechanisms identified (see F1.2). spec.md:132 asymmetry confirmed.\n+- Q2 (iteration 2): 41 grep hits in reverse direction but only ~12 CODE sites (uniform mechanism) + 1 absolute shell-out (replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs:26) + ~28 test-fixture/comment strings needing semantic review. Forward: ~40+ absolute-string sites + 1 relative require.\n+- Q3 (iteration 2): Net NEUTRAL. node_modules tooling-borrow already shipped (runtime has own node_modules). Only the artifact-root.cjs LOGIC seam remains, +1 hop post-merge. Keep the borrow, fix the hop, document the seam.\n \n ## What Worked\n \n - Mechanism-classification audit (iteration 1): separating absolute-string sites from relative-require sites exposed that the plan conflates them. 8-10 file reads + targeted rg gave full coverage.\n+- system-spec-kit surface enumeration (iteration 2): reading vitest.config.ts + package.json test:council + the council-playbook anchor test caught the 4→9 undercount that a grep-only audit would miss.\n \n ## What Failed\n \n (none yet)\n@@ -57,12 +60,14 @@\n ## Ruled-Out Directions\n \n - R1.1 (iteration 1): Single mechanical find/replace across all coupling — breaks class A absolute-string sites.\n - R1.2 (iteration 1): Treating reverse direction as larger per-site risk — uniform mechanism; forward single site riskier.\n+- R2.1 (iteration 2): Mechanism A (absolute-string) is forward-only — refuted by replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs:26 reverse shell-out.\n+- R2.2 (iteration 2): \"4 system-spec-kit edits suffice for REQ-003\" — real surface ~9 sites/5 files.\n \n ## Next Focus\n \n-Iteration 2: Complete Q2's coupling-COUNT and Q3's tooling-borrow depth math. Verify whether class (D) reverse sites ALL follow the uniform 3→2 / 4→3 pattern with zero exceptions, and compute the exact post-merge `__dirname` arithmetic for the artifact-root.cjs +1-hop and the system-spec-kit test:council include-glob impact (REQ-003 risk). Resolves Q2 and Q3.\n+Iteration 3: Q4 reference-migration surface — enumerate commands/.opencode/agents/.claude/agents, root + skill READMEs, the mk-deep-loop-guard plugin, git hooks, CI, and (highest-risk) system-skill-advisor routing corpus (labeled-prompts.jsonl, divergence ledger, hardcoded scorer constants). Quantify the ~948-hit surface from spec.md:88 and assess incomplete-migration risk per surface. Resolves Q4.\n \n ## Research Boundaries\n \n - Max iterations: 5\n","filediff":{"file":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/glm52-3/deep-research-strategy.md","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/glm52-3/deep-research-strategy.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/glm52-3/deep-research-strategy.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/glm52-3/deep-research-strategy.md\n@@ -40,12 +40,15 @@\n \n ## Answered Questions\n \n - Q1 (iteration 1): Mechanically safe. Runtime relocates as self-contained `runtime/` subtree. THREE distinct path-repair mechanisms identified (see F1.2). spec.md:132 asymmetry confirmed.\n+- Q2 (iteration 2): 41 grep hits in reverse direction but only ~12 CODE sites (uniform mechanism) + 1 absolute shell-out (replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs:26) + ~28 test-fixture/comment strings needing semantic review. Forward: ~40+ absolute-string sites + 1 relative require.\n+- Q3 (iteration 2): Net NEUTRAL. node_modules tooling-borrow already shipped (runtime has own node_modules). Only the artifact-root.cjs LOGIC seam remains, +1 hop post-merge. Keep the borrow, fix the hop, document the seam.\n \n ## What Worked\n \n - Mechanism-classification audit (iteration 1): separating absolute-string sites from relative-require sites exposed that the plan conflates them. 8-10 file reads + targeted rg gave full coverage.\n+- system-spec-kit surface enumeration (iteration 2): reading vitest.config.ts + package.json test:council + the council-playbook anchor test caught the 4→9 undercount that a grep-only audit would miss.\n \n ## What Failed\n \n (none yet)\n@@ -57,12 +60,14 @@\n ## Ruled-Out Directions\n \n - R1.1 (iteration 1): Single mechanical find/replace across all coupling — breaks class A absolute-string sites.\n - R1.2 (iteration 1): Treating reverse direction as larger per-site risk — uniform mechanism; forward single site riskier.\n+- R2.1 (iteration 2): Mechanism A (absolute-string) is forward-only — refuted by replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs:26 reverse shell-out.\n+- R2.2 (iteration 2): \"4 system-spec-kit edits suffice for REQ-003\" — real surface ~9 sites/5 files.\n \n ## Next Focus\n \n-Iteration 2: Complete Q2's coupling-COUNT and Q3's tooling-borrow depth math. Verify whether class (D) reverse sites ALL follow the uniform 3→2 / 4→3 pattern with zero exceptions, and compute the exact post-merge `__dirname` arithmetic for the artifact-root.cjs +1-hop and the system-spec-kit test:council include-glob impact (REQ-003 risk). Resolves Q2 and Q3.\n+Iteration 3: Q4 reference-migration surface — enumerate commands/.opencode/agents/.claude/agents, root + skill READMEs, the mk-deep-loop-guard plugin, git hooks, CI, and (highest-risk) system-skill-advisor routing corpus (labeled-prompts.jsonl, divergence ledger, hardcoded scorer constants). Quantify the ~948-hit surface from spec.md:88 and assess incomplete-migration risk per surface. Resolves Q4.\n \n ## Research Boundaries\n \n - Max iterations: 5\n","additions":6,"deletions":1},"truncated":false},"title":".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/glm52-3/deep-research-strategy.md","time":{"start":1783488707470,"end":1783488707472}},"id":"prt_f4035fb8b001s0HE8M3lmrlcQn","sessionID":"ses_0bfd247cdffejTvcrmloecAup3","messageID":"msg_f403599cb001KgeoPq01KvLx6h"}}
