{"type":"text","timestamp":1783489116682,"sessionID":"ses_0bfd247cdffejTvcrmloecAup3","part":{"id":"prt_f403c149f001C3E3yjYNQ8h52n","messageID":"msg_f403bdc33001669scF6onNM5fF","sessionID":"ses_0bfd247cdffejTvcrmloecAup3","type":"text","text":"All 5 questions answered at iteration 4. Convergence check: minIterations(3) met, newInfoRatio trend (0.85→0.70→0.62→0.45) above threshold, coverage gate passes (5/5), quality gate passes (8+ diverse sources). **Legal STOP → synthesis.** Updating todos and finalizing registry/strategy.","time":{"start":1783489107103,"end":1783489116681}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783489116684,"sessionID":"ses_0bfd247cdffejTvcrmloecAup3","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"edit","callID":"call_20398a40eeeb425583176651","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/glm52-3/deep-research-strategy.md","newString":"- Q4 (iteration 3): Surface = ~780+ non-history lines (commands 452, advisor 264, agents 18×2, plugins 3, ci 1). Advisor ALREADY has a merge-identity layer (aliases.ts:92-109); system-deep-loop is the SECOND fold (id-rename of MERGED_DEEP_SKILL_ID). Divergence-ledger reason strings are historical narration needing manual review (REQ-007). skill-graph.json is generated (edit sources + re-scan, don't hand-edit).\n- Q5 (iteration 4): DEFER. Zero production callers repo-wide; today's failure path is same-model retry-and-salvage (fanout-pool.cjs), not model-swap. fallback-router relocates as-is with zero merge-blocking dependency and no router-contract debt. Keep optional child 004.","oldString":"- Q4 (iteration 3): Surface = ~780+ non-history lines (commands 452, advisor 264, agents 18×2, plugins 3, ci 1). Advisor ALREADY has a merge-identity layer (aliases.ts:92-109); system-deep-loop is the SECOND fold (id-rename of MERGED_DEEP_SKILL_ID). Divergence-ledger reason strings are historical narration needing manual review (REQ-007). skill-graph.json is generated (edit sources + re-scan, don't hand-edit)."},"output":"Edit applied successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"diff":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/glm52-3/deep-research-strategy.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/glm52-3/deep-research-strategy.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/glm52-3/deep-research-strategy.md\n@@ -43,8 +43,9 @@\n - Q1 (iteration 1): Mechanically safe. Runtime relocates as self-contained `runtime/` subtree. THREE distinct path-repair mechanisms identified (see F1.2). spec.md:132 asymmetry confirmed.\n - Q2 (iteration 2): 41 grep hits in reverse direction but only ~12 CODE sites (uniform mechanism) + 1 absolute shell-out (replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs:26) + ~28 test-fixture/comment strings needing semantic review. Forward: ~40+ absolute-string sites + 1 relative require.\n - Q3 (iteration 2): Net NEUTRAL. node_modules tooling-borrow already shipped (runtime has own node_modules). Only the artifact-root.cjs LOGIC seam remains, +1 hop post-merge. Keep the borrow, fix the hop, document the seam.\n - Q4 (iteration 3): Surface = ~780+ non-history lines (commands 452, advisor 264, agents 18×2, plugins 3, ci 1). Advisor ALREADY has a merge-identity layer (aliases.ts:92-109); system-deep-loop is the SECOND fold (id-rename of MERGED_DEEP_SKILL_ID). Divergence-ledger reason strings are historical narration needing manual review (REQ-007). skill-graph.json is generated (edit sources + re-scan, don't hand-edit).\n+- Q5 (iteration 4): DEFER. Zero production callers repo-wide; today's failure path is same-model retry-and-salvage (fanout-pool.cjs), not model-swap. fallback-router relocates as-is with zero merge-blocking dependency and no router-contract debt. Keep optional child 004.\n \n ## What Worked\n \n - Mechanism-classification audit (iteration 1): separating absolute-string sites from relative-require sites exposed that the plan conflates them. 8-10 file reads + targeted rg gave full coverage.\n","filediff":{"file":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development