on 4): DEFER. Zero production callers repo-wide; today's failure path is same-model retry-and-salvage (fanout-pool.cjs), not model-swap. fallback-router relocates as-is with zero merge-blocking dependency and no router-contract debt. Keep optional child 004.\n \n ## What Worked\n \n - Mechanism-classification audit (iteration 1): separating absolute-string sites from relative-require sites exposed that the plan conflates them. 8-10 file reads + targeted rg gave full coverage.\n","additions":1,"deletions":0},"truncated":false},"title":".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/glm52-3/deep-research-strategy.md","time":{"start":1783489116683,"end":1783489116684}},"id":"prt_f403c3a05001Ja4nLJBAqiicjV","sessionID":"ses_0bfd247cdffejTvcrmloecAup3","messageID":"msg_f403bdc33001669scF6onNM5fF"}}
